-A python string is a list of characters enclosed inside single double or triple quotes 
  'string'
  "string"
  '''multiline string'''
-Accesing a character in string
  string = "Hello World"
  print(string[0]) -->it will print:H
-Finding length of string
  print(len(string)) -->it will print:11
-Find a character in string:finds the first occurance of character
  --find():it retuns -1 when character not found in string
    print(string.find('l')) -->it will print:2
  --index():raise a exception when charcter not found in string
    print(string.index('l'))-->it will print:2
-Find frequency of a character
  --count
    print(string.count('l'))-->it will print:3
-String Slicing
  --string_name[start_index : end_index : step]
    print(string[0:5])-->it will print:Hello
-Split a string
  --split()
    print(string(" "))-->it will print:["Hello", "World"]
-Check wheather a string starts or ends with a character
  --.startswith()
    string.startswith('H')-->it will print:True
  --.endswith()
    string.endswith('H')-->it will print:False
-Repeat a string multiple times
  print(string*2)-->it will print:Hello WorldHello World
-Replace a substring
  --.replace(old,new)
    new_string = string.replace("World","Reader")
    print(new_string)-->it will print:Hello Reader
-Changing the case
  --UPPERCASE
    print(string.upper())-->HELLO WORLD
  --lowercase
    print(string.lower())-->hello world
  --TitleCase
    print(string.title())-->Hello World
  --Capitalize
    print(string.capitalize())-->Hello world
  --swapcase
    print(string.swapcase())-->hELLO wORLD
-Reverse a string
  --we use join and reversed()
    print("".join(reversed(string)))-->dlroW olleH
-strip a string
  --.strip():it will strip off space at start and end
  --.lstrip():it will strip off space at starting 
  --.rstrip():it will strip off space at end  
-concatinate strings
  --we use + operator to do this
-Check properties of string
  word = "Hello World"
  word.isalnum() #check if all char are alphanumeric 
  word.isalpha() #check if all char in the string are alphabetic
  word.isdigit() #test if string contains digits
  word.istitle() #test if string contains title words
  word.isupper() #test if string contains upper case
  word.islower() #test if string contains lower case
  word.isspace() #test if string contains spaces
  word.endswith('d') #test if string endswith a d
  word.startswith('H') #test if string startswith H
